"red-billed-firefinch":{n:"Red-billed Firefinch",c:"Bird",s:"Finch",sz:"Small",cl:"Red",i:"ğŸ¦",wp:"Red-billed_firefinch",d:"A tiny finch with males displaying rich crimson-red plumage and a distinctive red bill. Females are brown with a red rump and facial wash. Common throughout sub-Saharan Africa, often near human habitation. The primary host of the village indigobird, a brood parasite.",w:"8-12 g",l:"10-11 cm",life:"5-8 years",act:"Diurnal",diet:"Granivore â€” grass seeds, small insects",cs:"Least Concern"},
"blue-waxbill":{n:"Blue Waxbill",c:"Bird",s:"Finch",sz:"Small",cl:"Blue",i:"ğŸ¦",wp:"Blue_waxbill",d:"A delicate, pale blue finch with a powder-blue face and breast, brown back, and a red bill. One of the most attractive of all African waxbills. Gregarious, usually found in small flocks feeding on the ground on grass seeds near water.",w:"8-12 g",l:"12-14 cm",life:"5-8 years",act:"Diurnal",diet:"Granivore â€” grass seeds, small insects",cs:"Least Concern"},
"violet-eared-waxbill":{n:"Violet-eared Waxbill",c:"Bird",s:"Finch",sz:"Small",cl:"Brown & Violet",i:"ğŸ¦",wp:"Violet-eared_waxbill",d:"An exquisite small finch with brown plumage, a red bill, red forehead, and distinctive violet-blue ear patches. Found in dry thornveld and woodland edges. Shy and easily overlooked despite its colourful markings. Forages on the ground in small groups.",w:"8-13 g",l:"11-13 cm",life:"5-8 years",act:"Diurnal",diet:"Granivore â€” grass seeds, small insects",cs:"Least Concern"},
