"cape-parrot":{n:"Cape Parrot",c:"Bird",s:"Parrot",sz:"Medium",cl:"Green",i:"ğŸ¦œ",wp:"Cape_parrot",d:"South Africa's only endemic parrot with olive-green plumage and orange-red shoulder patches. Critically dependent on yellowwood forest for nesting and feeding. With fewer than 1,600 remaining in the wild, it is one of the rarest parrots in Africa.",w:"260-370 g",l:"30-36 cm",life:"30-60 years",act:"Diurnal",diet:"Herbivore â€” yellowwood fruit, nuts, seeds",cs:"Vulnerable"},
